The paper deals with a stochastic optimization problem related to scheduling, which involves packing items into bins subject to capacity constraints. This problem is of interest in several areas of computer science, including operations research, machine learning, and robotics. The paper presents new results on the performance of different policies for solving the problem, including non-anticipatory policies, fractional assignment policies, and fixed assignment policies. The analysis involves techniques from approximation algorithms, online algorithms, and probability theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
